<font size=2>TOP/Our Technology/DGDS&reg; ....</font><p>
<B>DGDS&reg; Characteristics</B>
<P>
<font size=2 color=#333333>
<B>DGDS&reg; makes it possible to release a bioactive volatile component only in stable condition.</B><P>
<img src=../img/dgdsz1_e2.GIF width=270 height=122 align=right>
The form of DGDS&reg; is made out of cotton and non-woven fabric outside, and seat-shaped material inside which is made by various bases and capsule which is kept by carbon coating, using special PVA at the core as adsorption carrier for volatile component.<P>

When a product of DGDS&reg; is put on the skin, volatile component contained in the capsule becomes gas by the effect of H<sub>2</sub>O in the air and the insensible perspiration, which takes bioactive volatile component into the body safely and steadily.<P>

At this time, because it doesn't touch skin directly due to the cover of non-woven fabric, other various substrate inside the fabric doesn't come into the body. Then, only active ingredient (volatile component) comes into the body. <P>


<B>No burden and nonirritating to the skin (safety to the skin)</B><P>
<img src=../img/eri.gif width=120 height=91 align=left>
Unlike the basis of oil, cream, compress and ointment, the product with DGDS&reg; never make any substrate except medicinal properties contact the skin due to its mechanism.<P>

Because of that, even when a problem like a rash of the skin occurs in the treatment of other transdermal absorption, such a problem doesn't occur if it is DGDS&reg;. We have carried out a skin irritation study which is accordant to GCP (Good Clinical Practice).
<P><BR>

<B>Quality doesn't deteriorate easily, and stable.(The stability of the quality)</B><P>

Oils and fats except for the active ingredient are not cotained in the product of DGDS&reg;. Therefore, the problem like a deterioration of quality due to the propagation of bacteria by water and the oxidization of oil and fat element which would occur in the dosage form of a general transdermal absorption doesn't occur.
<P>
There is no deterioration of the quality until it contacts air and the administration of active element starts.
<P>
<B>The long and stable administration of volatile component in moderate quantities.(The durability of element release)
</B><P>

In case the dilution ratio is specified as (principal agent weight)/((base weight)+(additive weight)), it becomes high concentration of 10-2 to 10-3 in general dosage form.<P>

The highest and efficient dilution ratio is expected, when it is lower quantity.  Actually, with DGDS&reg;, it is diluted by air and administrated in the concentration of 10-6 - 10-7.<P>

And, the effect lasts steadily for a long time by vaporizing the active ingredient in the capsule by using technology which makes the heat of adsorption of water in the air steady at a suitable temperature.
<P></font>					</td></tr>
